						               													<description>This game for Ages 3 and up and premiered at Essen 2000.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Included are 19 various wooden play figures, mainly animals, and 10 game markers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the first game the pieces are laid out in plain sight of all.  An older player reads a story and when any of the figures is named, each player tries to be the first to grab it. If the figure has already been named, the player takes a marker instead.  At the end of the story the player with the most pieces wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the second game, the pieces are laid out in an order and the player must identify them to get a point.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The last game is one of remembering which pieces have been named.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is similar to the earlier Ratz-Fatz and some of the scenarios can be used to make a larger combined game, so in some ways this is an expansion kit.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Integrates with:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Ratz-Fatz&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
